LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE SENATE
SENATE BILL NO. 1179
BY JUDICIARY AND RULES COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO HEALTH AND SAFETY; AMENDING SECTION 39-912, IDAHO CODE, AS
3 AMENDED IN SECTION 13 OF SENATE BILL NO. 1014, AS ENACTED BY THE FIRST
4 REGULAR SESSION OF THE SIXTY-EIGHTH IDAHO LEGISLATURE, TO REVISE PROVI-
5 SIONS REGARDING EXEMPTIONS; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN
6 EFFECTIVE DATE.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. That Section 39-912, Idaho Code, as amended in Section 13 of
9 Senate Bill No. 1014, as enacted by the First Regular Session of the Sixty-
10 eighth Idaho Legislature, be, and the same is hereby amended to read as fol-
11 lows:
12 39-907. EXEMPTIONS BECAUSE OF RELIGIOUS BELIEF. The provisions of
13 this chapter shall not apply to any child whose parent or guardian: objects
14 thereto on the grounds that it conflicts with the tenets or practices of a
15 recognized church or religious denomination of which said parent or guardian
16 is an adherent or member.
17 (1) Objects on religious or other grounds, including philosophical or
18 conscientious beliefs; or
19 (2) Submits a certificate signed by a physician licensed by the state
20 board of medicine stating that the physical condition of the child is such
21 that all or any of the requirements of this chapter would endanger the life or
22 health of the child.
23 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
24 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
25 July 1, 2025.

